There may be an issue with one or more settings in your DocuSign account. The user whose credentials are used to enable the integration between DocuSign for Salesforce and DocuSign (sometimes known as the SOBO user) must have all of the following permissions and flags checked; "Can Manage Account", "Can Send Envelope", "Allow Send on Behalf Of", and "API Account Wide Access". All of these setting may be accessed by logging directly in to DocuSign, clicking Preferences, and selecting the Permissions area of the Administration console. Unless all of those settings are enabled, the integration will not function properly. It is possible the issue is unrelated to these settings, but these must be checked first. Please contact your DocuSign administrator to verify whether any settings have recently changed in DocuSign.

Here are a few things you'll need to complete your template configuration:
You’ll copy and paste anchor text into your files to dynamically insert Salesforce data and DocuSign fields.
You’ll need to have at least one Salesforce data source and the fields you want added to your document.
You can also add DocuSign fields, such as signature or date signed into your Word templates.

Select your main data source

Select the data source where your users will begin generating documents. For example, if you choose Opportunity, users can pull data from an Opportunity and related objects, like Account.

Need Help?

Find out more about template configurations in the DocuSign Support Center.

Add Salesforce fields

Salesforce fields allow you to dynamically populate information on your document directly from Salesforce. For example, if you selected Account as your main data source, you may want to pull Account Name or Billing Address. Be sure to copy and paste the corresponding anchor text into your Word templates. Decide formatting and conditional options in the dropdown menu.

Add DocuSign fields

You can also have DocuSign fields, like signature, automatically prepared for recipients. Be sure to copy and paste the corresponding anchor text into your Word templates.

Upload Word templates

Upload all of the Word templates for this configuration. For each template, you can choose a suffix option for generated documents . You can also decide if users should generate a Word document or a PDF.

Determine bulk document creation option

If you’ve uploaded multiple Word templates with this configuration, you can choose if all documents should be generated every time. By default, users can select which ones they want to generate. However, if your users need to generate all documents, then select Bulk Document Creation.

Test your templates

Choose data sources from Salesforce and click Preview to generate example documents.

Review and update

Check your documents in Word to confirm text placement and formatting.You can update your templates by going back to any previous step in this configuration wizard without losing your progress.

Determine your button label

Give your button a descriptive label, such as Generate Sales Order.

Select page layouts and deployment option

Decide where your button should appear and select to deploy as a Detail Page Button (Salesforce Classic) or Quick Action (Lightning Experience). If you don’t want a button on any layout, deselect all layout options before clicking Create Button. Your button will be available in the Salesforce Object Manager setup.
